Prove (3.44b) p ⋁ (¬p ⋀ q) ≡ p ⋁ q

  p ⋁ (¬p ⋀ q)
=    〈 golden rule 〉
  p ⋁ (¬p ≡ q ≡ ¬p ⋁ q)
=    〈 distributivity of ⋁ over ≡ 〉
  p ⋁ ¬p ≡ p ⋁ q ≡ p ⋁ ¬p ⋁ q
=    〈 excluded middle, twice 〉
  true ≡ p ⋁ q ≡ true ⋁ q
=    〈 zero of ⋁ 〉
  true ≡ p ⋁ q ≡ true
=    〈 identity of ≡, twice 〉
  p ⋁ q ╱╱


-- OR --


  p ⋁ (¬p ⋀ q)
=    〈 distributivity of ⋁ over ⋀ 〉
  (p ⋁ ¬p) ⋀ (p ⋁ q)
=    〈 excluded middle 〉
  true ⋀ (p ⋁ q)
=    〈 identity of ⋀ 〉
  p ⋁ q ╱╱
